             Four people died in southeast Turkey
in a mine explosion that authorities blamed on the Kurdistan
Workersâ€™ Party, or PKK, state news agency Anatolia reported.  
 The explosion took place soon after PKK members had set
fire to an oil well in the province of Batman, the agency
